Description: 2005 Epiphone G400 1966 SG Standard Limited Edition Custom Shop Korea MIK It has the “Limited Edition Custom Shop” logo on the headstock. It has the full wrap around pickguard. The tuners on the 1966 model have changed back and forth between the original Grovers you see here and Kluson types. All original. No issues. More recent versions have the “Alnico Classic” PU's. This has the HotCH (14k)/57CH (8.5k) Alnico 5 combo that were standard equipment on the higher end models (LP Standards and G400s) of the late 90's and out into the 00's. Built in Korea in 2005. (“U05…...” = Unsung Korea 2005) A couple finish dings, the worst being behind the bridge (pictured) and a small one at the tip of the lower horn. Minor fret wear on the first couple frets under the plain strings. Otherwise very little player wear.
